\par \plain\fs18\cf2 TPJCBViewer notifies the user of changes to the Windows clipbaord.
\par 
\par \plain\fs18\cf2\b Unit\plain\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\fs18\cf2 PJCBView\plain\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\fs18\cf2 This component hooks itself into the Windows clipboard viewer chain and receives notifications from Windows whenever the contents of the clipboard change. When a change is detected the \plain\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\fs18\cf2 OnClipboardChanged\plain\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\fs18\cf2  event is triggered.
\par \plain\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\fs18\cf2 The component also provides an \plain\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\fs18\cf2 Enabled\plain\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\fs18\cf2  property which disables the triggering of \plain\fs18\cf2\i OnClipboardChanged\plain\fs18\cf2  events when false. It also has a \plain\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\fs18\cf2 TriggerOnCreation\plain\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\fs18\cf2  property which, when true, causes the \plain\fs18\cf2\i OnClipboardChanged\plain\fs18\cf2  event to be triggered immediately after the control has been created as well as when the clipboard contents change.
\par }

